# SEO Guidelines

## Hosting & SEO Limits

- The site is a **client-rendered Vite SPA** hosted on **GitHub Pages**
- There is no SSR, so:
  - Initial HTML is mostly the root shell from `index.html`
  - Some crawlers may not execute client-side JavaScript
- SEO work focuses on:
  - High-quality baseline metadata in `index.html`
  - Clean URLs, internal linking, and semantics
  - Fast, stable layout (LCP/CLS)

## Baseline Metadata (`index.html`)

- `index.html` defines the default:
  - `<title>`
  - `<meta name="description">`
  - Open Graph tags (`og:title`, `og:description`, `og:image`, `og:url`, `og:site_name`)
  - Twitter cards
  - Canonical URL
  - JSON-LD for the salon entity
- When editing `index.html`, keep these in sync with `translations.seo` where possible.

## Per-Page SEO with `usePageSEO`

- Hook: `src/hooks/usePageSEO.js`
- Usage pattern in pages:

```jsx
import { useLanguage } from '../contexts/LanguageContext'
import { translations } from '../translations'
import { usePageSEO } from '../hooks/usePageSEO'

export const AboutPage = () => {
  const { t } = useLanguage()

  usePageSEO({
    title: t(translations.seo.aboutTitle),
    description: t(translations.seo.aboutDescription)
  })

  return (
    <div className="page-content">
      {/* content */}
    </div>
  )
}
```

- `usePageSEO` updates:
  - `document.title`
  - `meta[name="description"]`
  - `meta[property="og:description"]`
  - `meta[name="twitter:description"]`
  - `meta[property="og:title"]`
  - `meta[name="twitter:title"]`

## Translated SEO Text

- All SEO strings live in `translations.seo` in `src/translations/index.js`
- For any new page or major section:
  - Add `Title` and `Description` entries for EN/BG under `translations.seo`
  - Use `t(translations.seo.someKey)` in the corresponding page with `usePageSEO`

## On-Page SEO Checklist for New Pages

- Unique, descriptive `title` and `description` via `usePageSEO`
- Semantic headings:
  - One main `<h1>` per page
  - Logical hierarchy of `<h2>`, `<h3>` for sections
- Images:
  - Use meaningful `alt` text where appropriate
  - Avoid layout shifts by constraining width/height via CSS
- Links:
  - Use `Link` from `react-router-dom` for internal navigation
  - Ensure important pages are reachable via internal links from the homepage

## Performance & UX (SEO-Relevant)

- Optimize Largest Contentful Paint (LCP):
  - Avoid blocking the hero area with unnecessary scripts
  - Prefer Vite imports and code-splitting for non-critical sections
- Avoid Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS):
  - Reserve space for hero, sliders, and gallery using fixed heights or aspect-ratio containers
  - Do not inject large DOM blocks above the fold after initial render
- Use `loading="lazy"` on non-critical images (e.g., galleries, preview cards)

## Structured Data

- The primary JSON-LD for the salon lives in `index.html`
- When adjusting services or hours:
  - Prefer updating the JSON-LD in `index.html` to keep the canonical entity accurate
- Route-specific JSON-LD is optional; if added, ensure it:
  - Mirrors the same entity (no conflicting data)
  - Is injected only once per page

